wikipedia_page.main: William James Audsley (1833–1907) was an architect and a medical doctor of Scottish descent.

response: * George Ashdown Audsley & William Audsley (Liverpool based) designed Streatlam Tower (1871), 5 Princes Road; 92 Bold Street (1890s)
In 1860 he formed a partnership with the brothers George Ashdown Audsley and William Audsley of W. & G. Audsley. The partnership was terminated when the brothers opted to become independent in 1863.
